      "demo_behavior": "Module: TopModule I would like you to implement a module named TopModule with the following interface. All input and output ports are one bit unless otherwise specified. - input  clk - input  reset - input  data - output start_shifting The module should implement a finite-state machine that searches for the sequence 1101 in an input bit stream. When the sequence is found, it should set start_shifting to 1, forever, until reset. Reset is active high synchronous. Assume all sequential logic is triggered on the positive edge of the clock.\nKey rules: Implement behavior exactly as described in the prompt.\nReset: Only as explicitly described in the prompt.\nCorner cases: No additional corner cases beyond prompt requirements.\nPerformance: Use prompt-defined timing/latency behavior.",
